# ✅ Role‑Based Protection (Authorization)

### Example: Admin‑only routes

```ts
export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const role = request.cookies.get('role')?.value;
  const { pathname } = request.nextUrl;

  if (pathname.startsWith('/admin') && role !== 'admin') {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/403', request.url));
  }

  return NextResponse.next();
}
```

✅ Authorization before rendering  
✅ Secure by default

***

# ✅ Protect API Routes (Very Important)

Middleware also protects backend APIs.

```ts
export const config = {
  matcher: [
    '/dashboard/:path*',
    '/api/private/:path*',
  ],
};
```

✅ Single layer of protection  
✅ No duplicated auth logic

***

# ✅ JWT‑Based Authentication Example

```ts
import { jwtVerify } from 'jose';

export async function middleware(req: NextRequest) {
  const token = req.cookies.get('token')?.value;

  if (!token) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', req.url));
  }

  try {
    await jwtVerify(
      token,
      new TextEncoder().encode(process.env.JWT_SECRET)
    );
    return NextResponse.next();
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', req.url));
  }
}
```

✅ Validates token at the edge  
✅ Prevents invalid sessions early

